descriptiveMetadata.title: al-Qurʼān (ajzāʼ)
descriptiveMetadata.abstract:
Fragments of an Abbasid Qurʼān (probably third century A.H. / ninth century C.E.), containing verses from the Sura al-Muʾminūn (سورة المؤمنون), the complete Sura al-Nūr (سورة النور), and verses from the Sura al-Furqān (سورة الفرقان). The script seems to correspond to the Abbasid Style D.I as described by F. Deroche.


Featured in BBC Radio 4's
'In Our Time - The Written World'.
subject: Koran
